<br>
Triangle with vertices ABC.  A given point P.  Create lines AP, BP, CP.  Calculate the angles that result from this.  The angle formed of the lines AP&amp;BP, AP&amp;CP, and BP&amp;CP.  <br>
<br>
Sum up the angles.<br>
<br>
If the sum is 360 degrees the point is in or on the given triangle.  <br>
<br>
Else it is outside the triangle (the sum will be less than 360 I think).<br>
<br>
